  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Engineer (M&E Contractor)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Support, manage and coordinate Mechanical works and services for building construction projects for a well-established M&amp;E Contractor (MNC Company)</li>\n  <li>Plan, develop, and manage work schedules to ensure tasks are completed on time.</li>\n  <li>Prepare progress reports for clients and project managers, detailing delays, defects, and necessary rectification measures for Mechanical works.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical guidance and resolve Mechanical-related issues efficiently.</li>\n  <li>Report on Mechanical progress and arrange site inspections with contractors, subcontractors, and clerk-of-works.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 1-3 years of relevant experience with an M&amp;E Contractor</li>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Mechanical, Mechatronics or relevant engineering discipline</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge of Project execution processes.</li>\n  <li>Advanced knowledge of local code of practice of design implementation.</li>\n  <li>Local construction knowledge</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
